**Solution 1:** Decimate a full cow into digestible pieces.
This solution involves taking a whole cow and breaking it down into smaller, digestible parts. This is precisely what a butcher shop does – they process whole animals (typically beef, pork, lamb, etc.) into cuts of meat, bones, and other products.

Both solutions describe processes that are relevant to a butcher shop. However, the question asks which solution is *more* appropriate. Since a butcher shop primarily deals with land animals (cows, pigs, sheep, etc.), and Solution 1 directly reflects this core function, it is the more appropriate solution.

